

Important commands for debug and code generation:-

1.  " npx playwright test --debug " opens playwright debugger and can be used  for step by step debugging

2. Most Efficient tool for Automatic code generation by just debugging and running on website:-

    npx playwright codegen https://google.com

    Any testing link which you have to write code for should be written after codegen commands

3. In playwright.config.js file you can see below format 

    use: {
   
    /* Collect trace when retrying the failed test. See https://playwright.dev/docs/trace-viewer */
    trace: 'retain-on-failure', // off , on, , retain-on-failure
    headless:true,
    screenshot:'on'
  },


  There you can use "https://playwright.dev/docs/trace-viewer" and upload trace zip file under test-results folder or it can be found on show repots html page which can be uploaded on trace website and can be debug steo by step which help us to find where and how the actual test case failed.
  
